datastructures.queues

Interface PriorityQueue<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>, Queue<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    HeapPriorityQueue, LinearPriorityQueue

    public interface PriorityQueue<T>
extends Queue<T>
    A PriorityQueue is an extension of a Queue. Instead of classical FIFO processing, a PriorityQueue inserts elements with a higher priority first, where "higher" is typically interpreted as "lower" in the arithmetic sense, e.g 1 is "higher" priority than 2. Elements with the same priority are inserted in a FIFO fashion. The PriorityQueue interface extends the Queue interface by overriding the enqueue() method to allow for the addition of an extra parameter, which encodes the priority of the node in the data structure.
    Since:
    October 2013
    Author:
    Jason Filippou (jasonfil@cs.umd.edu)
